  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, we can find that Equation 5 and Equation 6 share the same paradigm:",
    "where W ∈ R r×r and we define W as the weight of mixer to fuse the subspaces.",
    "For vanilla LoRA, the mixer is the fixed identity matrix fusing r subspaces.",
    "For the two-subspaces-mixing LoRA, the mixer is a fixed butterfly factor fusing 2r subspaces, which is more than LoRA.",
    "Therefore, we propose MoSLoRA, adapting a trainable mixer to fuse all the possible subspaces."
